  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a study to detect the sensitivity of thyromental distance ratio as a single predictor
      for difficult intubation in patients undergoing cesarean section under general anesthesia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The authors intend to use the HMDR for detection of difficult intubation in parturient
      undergoing cesarean section that is either elective or emergency.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
